name: Lucky 13 5.5" glass nail file
description:
Looking for a new nail file? We've got you covered! 5.5" long, 4" usable grit, and comes in a vinyl sleeve to keep from getting snagged!

I highly suggest investing in a $1 toothbrush holder (I got mine from Target) if you're planning on keeping this in a purse or bag. Stuff a couple jumbo cotton balls in either end and toss in your file and some nail clippers, you're good to go and ready for anything!

One nail file of a random color will be included with orders over $50 pre-shipping/after discounts.

name: Clearance Polishes and Pigments
description: See here for larger images and more details. Each polish except for Green is in perfect condition, it just didn't meet the idea I had in mind. Green was made using a pigment that didn't dissolve completely into the lacquer and the occasional tiny chunk may come out on the brush, thus the price is further lowered. -------- Clearance pigments and jellies. Two photos of the pigments are used to get a better idea of the color. Up to 2 "dash" have been used of the pigments, still leaving the bags nearly completely full. 1 OZ COSMETIC FLUORESCENT BLUE VIOLET: DO NOT USE IN POLISH. Great for soap or non-lacquer cosmetics; will not disperse in lacquer base. 1 OZ CHROMIUM OXIDE GREEN: Lacquer-safe; same pigment used to make the green jelly. Be sure to mix thoroughly into base. If you order the Chromium Oxide Green pigment and the Green jellie I will include the "recipe" to make the Green jellie. 1 OZ TITANIUM DIOXIDE WHITE: DO NOT USE IN POLISH. Great for soap or non-lacquer cosmetics; will not disperse in lacquer base. 1 OZ BLACK OXIDE: Unsure how it will react in lacquer base. Magnetic but not sure how it will react as far as usual "magnetic" lacquers. Completely unused. 1 OZ COSMETIC FLUORESCENT YOLK YELLOW: Lacquer-safe. Be sure to mix thoroughly into base. 1/2 OZ GREEN JELLIE: About half full. Made using Chromium Oxide Green pigment. If you order the Chromium Oxide Green pigment and the Green jellie I will include the "recipe" to make the Green jellie.

name: Butterfly Project
description: Important: Please do not use promo codes with this product as it is a charity lacquer. Instead, please order the rest of your products as usual and then make a separate order with only one to two bottles of this lacquer and use the code COMBINESHIPPING for free shipping. If you are ordering more than two bottles please simply make a second order with all the charity lacquers you wish and do not use any promo code. Purple base with silver holographic butterflies and a rainbow of fine and medium hex glitters. Butterfly Project is Lucky 13's first Pay What You Can polish. There will be a range of options available from $2 to $20 (before shipping costs); all will receive the same 15ml bottle. Please contribute what you can as larger contributions will be used to offset the costs of those who are unable to afford it but are still in need of Butterfly Project as a self harm alternative. Your contribution may save a life! If you are in need of Butterfly Project as a self harm alternative and cannot afford a monetary payment please contact me and we will arrange creative forms of payment. Draw me a picture, write me a short story or a poem, promise me you'll blog about it or talk to friends about it, raise funds using MTurk and send me an Amazon gift card...Whatever! We'll work something out <3 If you want a custom name, something you call your butterfly, or if you would like me to name your bottle of Butterfly Project for you please leave that information in the Notes field when you order. See the final picture for how a named bottle will look--Mr. Waffles is my Butterfly. Please note, due to the heavier than normal weight of the butterflies they may sink when sitting on your shelf. To redistribute them make sure the cap is on securely (but not overtightened!) and set the bottle upside down on your desk for 5 minutes before using. Click here to read my story. Note: $10 is the recommended amount for this polish; it will cover the cost of supplies for your bottle and will cover supplies for one person who is in need but unable to afford it.

Uh oh, did I just mix Gollum/Smeagol and Smaug there? Smaug, Smeagol, same diff, right? ;-) Inspired by Smaug. See review here.

Inspired by the Balrog. See review here.

name: Fight Like a Girl
description: Important: Please do not use promo codes with this product as it is a charity lacquer. Instead, please order the rest of your products as usual and then make a separate order with only one to two bottles of this lacquer and use the code COMBINESHIPPING for free shipping. If you are ordering more than two bottles please simply make a second order with all the charity lacquers you wish and do not use any promo code. Hot pink jelly base with tiny purple shimmer and different sizes and shapes of dark purple glitter. My soul sister, Mandi, a nurse and a wonderful mother, was recently diagnosed with breast cancer. It has developed to a point where the best course of action is a double mastectomy. Because of the costs involved and because she'll be unable to work while she's recovering I'm doing what I can to support her--and that's spreading awareness and donating 50% of each bottle sold to her, her little boy Skylur (who's almost 5), and her wonderful husband Greg. Mandi has been through so many difficult times in her life but has never lost her optimism or her beautiful smile. She touches the hearts of so many, she's truly an inspiration to me. I want to be like her when I grow up!! :-) $4 from every full size and $3 from every shortie will be donated to Mandi. If all you can afford is kind thoughts, prayers, and remembering how cancer affects so many that is help enough <3

name: Revenge is Suede
description:
Suede shimmer in a matte base.

Do you still lust after matte suede polishes like the ones OPI made (but are always so DARN expensive and hard to find)? Well, now you can make ANY creme polish a matte suede with this topcoat! You can even wear it over a duo-chrome for even more of a unique look!

This polish looks best over darker shades but even over lighter shades it looks lovely.

Want to know the coolest part about Revenge is Suede? I'm sure you all know how notorious matte/suede polishes are for chipping if you so much as look at them the wrong way, right? I wore "real" suede polishes on my thumbs for the mani above and the nails with Revenge is Suede lasted three days longer than the "real" suedes. I didn't even use a normal topcoat beforehand, either!

name: Unicorn Blood

Inspired by, of course, the liquid silver unicorn blood drunk by Quirrell to sustain Lord Voldemort's life. See a review here.

name: Golden Snitch

description: Take my love, take my land, take me where I cannot stand....I don't care, I'm still free, you can't take the sky from me Dark charcoal jelly base with microfine, small, and medium silver glitters. Inspired by Serenity herself and the space that she flies in. See review here and here.

description: I am a leaf on the wind, watch how I soar... Sky blue jelly base with tiny silver and medium light green glitters. Inspired by our favorite pilot, Wash. See review here and here.

name: No Power in the 'Verse Can Stop Me
description: Seafoam green jelly base with a hint of sky blue shimmer with tiny and medium silver and holo hot pink glitters. River has a gentle playfulness, a sense of innocence. How could anything other than vibrant Spring colors represent her? Inspired by River Tam. See review here.

description: The palest grey jelly with fine light and dark silver glitters. The Bible has some pretty specific things to say about killin'. It is, however, somewhat fuzzier on the subject of kneecaps...Inspired by Shepherd Book. See review here.

name: Special Hell
description: Fiery orange jelly base with holographic red squares and tiny ruby red hex. Thank goodness Mal didn't take advantage of Saffron, or he would have gone to the special Hell...Inspired by our Mrs. Reynolds, Yolanda/Saffron/Bridget. See review here.

name: Big-City Dandy
description: Black jelly base with indigo and purple microshimmer. Mal: Jayne, you will keep a civil tongue in that mouth, or I will sew it shut. Is there an understanding between us? Jayne: You don't pay me to talk pretty. Just because Kaylee gets lubed up over some big-city dandy doesn't mean... From the episode Serenity. Inspired by Simon. See review here.

name: Strawberry Girl
description: Strawberry red jelly with tiny black hex and green shreds. When you're stuck in space for weeks or months at a time, nothing is sweeter than a sweet, juicy, ripe strawberry. Inspired by Kaylee. See review here.

name: The Hero of Canton, the Man They Call Jayne
description: Small and medium matte red, orange, and yellow glitters in a clear base. Someone walks down the street wearing this polish, people know you're not afraid of anything. Inspired by Jayne. See review here.

name: Big Damn Hero
description: Tiny and medium red, find and medium light and dark browns in a clear base. Mal: Well look at this. Appears we got here just in the nick of time. What does that make us? Zo: Big damn heroes, sir. From the episode Safe Inspired by Captain Malcolm Reynolds. See review here.

name: Warrior Woman
description: Tiny bronze squares with teensy tiny taupe microflakes in a clear base. The flakes are SO hard to capture on camera but shimmer beautifully in the light. Wash: [very enthusiastically] Have you seen what she wears? Forget about it. Have you ever been with a warrior woman? From the episode Bushwhacked Inspired by Zo. See review here.

name: Wibbly Wobbly, Timey Wimey
description: Deep blue jelly base with tiny turquoise square and hex, tiny midnight blue, medium ocean blue, and silver holographic stars and moons. The Tenth Doctor explains time travel and the flow of time in a very...eloquent manner. See reviews here and here.

name: Quantum Locked
description: Light grey jelly base with silver shreds. The Weeping Angels of Doctor Who are quantum locked; they only exist when they're not being observed. In the sight of another living being they turn to stone; and you can't kill stone, can you? The Doctor has some excellent advicefor those who encounter Weeping Angels. See review here and here.

name: Bad Wolf
description: A deep charcoal grey, nearly black, jelly with rainbow microshimmer. Bad Wolf. The words that inspired Rose to save the Ninth Doctor See review here and here.

name: You Sexy Thing
description:
TARDIS blue creme with a slight frost finish.

It's the TARDIS. The best ship in the universe. And oh-so sexy! The Doctor himself calls the TARDIS sexy (but only when they're alone).

name: Life is Short and You are Hot
description: Hot pink jelly base with tiny maroon squares and medium holographic hot pink. One of my favorite lines from the episode "Blink". This episode is best known for the Weeping Angels, but Detective Inspector Shipton doesn't get nearly enough credit for this wonderful exchange. And face it, who doesn't want to be complimented by their nail polish? See review here, here, and here.

name: Companion Cube
description:
Grey jelly base with tiny pink, medium silver, and pink hearts.

The Companion Cube will always be your best friend.

Please note that since the hearts are comparatively heavy they can sink to the bottom. Just turn the bottle upside down and gently roll it to redistribute the hearts.

name: Song of Storms

name: Pride

Show your LGBT pride/support or just to show your love of color!

name: Faerie Wings

Generously donated by faerie elders to allow their beauty to live on!

name: Mystery Grab Bag (NOT Lucky 13s)
description: These grab bags may or may not include Lucky 13 polishes! These bags do NOT include exclusively L13L! Not sure what colors you want? Just want to get a random assortment of polish? Get a mystery grab bag! Each grab bag will include a minimum of $25 worth of items from this page and from my current (but unposted!) blog sale stash, with at least 1 full size OR 2 mini Indies OR 1 to 2 frankens and a variety of mainstream brands, though I have almost exclusively indies available now. I will take suggestions but this box cannot be 100% customized, where's the fun and mystery in that?? I will accept ONE specific request per mystery grab bag ordered, up to a $6 lacquer value. Email me with your preference or put it in the "notes" field during checkout. Lucky 13 orders and shipping will be combined with mystery grab bags. If this item is ordered alone there is free shipping to the US!

name: Simple customization
description:
Please contact me before adding this item to your cart. Please do not use any discount codes with this item.

This item is for any BASIC polish customization such as removing one of the glitters, removing a jelly base, adding a jelly base to an otherwise clear-base polish, etc.
